    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2f7854a3_bec82835",
        "filename": "src/gpu/gl/GrGLGpu.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 10
      },
      "lineNbr": 3804,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-09T21:15:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So we are moving trying to move to a world where on the public API we separate the idea of flush and submit. So the job of flush is send all things from Ganesh queued up buffers, to backend specific calls. Most backends will build up command buffers or equivalent during this time, GL being the outlier that sends calls to the driver (though really the driver is just recording things to its own buffer).\n\nSubmit says okay actually send all the work to the GPU now. For non GL backends this is pretty obvious what it does, it submits the buffers/encoders to the GPU. For GL the equivalent of this is glFlush and glFinish. This is why they are currently in GLs submit call.\n\nfinishFlush and onFinishFlush are not just about handling finishCallbacks, but they are also responsible for handling all the other state in GrFlushInfo (modulo syncing the CPU which will eventually be pulled off and passed in the submit call). It just happens to be that GL and Metal currently only care about the finish callback and don\u0027t need to know things for the others. Happy to rename the function to be something like handleFlushInfo and onHandleFlushInfo or something like that.",
      "parentUuid": "3aa36db2_34759061",
      "revId": "3b756461efcb9455858361d329acadb697e2b7cf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
